	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=196376><span id= >Grep</span></a><br><span id=notbold>6 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>1. It does not proc anything, focus effect takes place when spells are cast.<br><br>2. It does not create more hate.<br><br>3. It lessens spell hate by 25% (e.g. enchanter casts tash or slow right as mob is pulled, he will get aggro and very likely die in the planes if cleric does not have him symboled; or if he isn't runed).&nbsp;&nbsp;So...this focus effect lessens the hate that the enchanter will get, and thus will allow the enchanter to tash/slow a bit earlier than normal, and you don't necessarily need to wait for warrior's crap taunt or their weapons' proc taunt, nor paladins' stun taunt(which i love[speaking as a cleric here], paladins make amazing MA's due to stun taunt keeping such nice aggro).<br><br>4. This focus effect is an enchanters' dream in the planes, if only it reduced spell hate by at least 40%</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
