	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=101415><span id= >Rishaka</span></a><br><span id=notbold>52 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.13]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The damage bonus varies, and unlike bane or magic style damage, it is not added to the weapon base damage rating as far as I can tell.<br><br>It looks like the damage is totaled through whatever decadimentional math VI uses, then the bonus damage is added in as straight damage points.<br><br>So if you hit for 10 points, you end up doing 22 with the bonus damage listed.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>&nbsp;<br><br>Rishaka Scaledancer, Monk of the 38th Form - Striking Hand of the Honor of Knights guild.<br>Shabrinn Allfadahr, Beastlord of the 47th Season - Unguilded wanderer of Mother Luclin.</td></td></tr>
